ris Watterston for the work that has been carried out, including an additional cancellation fee of 30% of the total agreed project costs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">All invoices are submitted by email. Chris Watterston reserves the right to remove, disable or cancel the work or Services for Client from if payments are not received within 7 calendar days of invoice date.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">In the event that the Client fails to pay the Services invoice within the agreed payment date stated on the invoice, Chris Watterston reserves the right to apply the intrest of 8% above the Bank of England&#39;s base rate for each six month period, as stated under the Late Payment of Commercial Debts (Interest) Act 1998. Chris Watterston also reserves the right to apply an additional amount of compensate for the costs of collecting late payments, as stated under section 5A of the Late Payment of Commercial Debts (Interest) Act 1998.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">All invoices, quotations and proposals are in British Pound Sterling (GBP).<br />\r\nUnder the event that the Client is not making payment from within the United Kingdom or in British Pound Sterling (GBP), the Client agrees that the total amount must be paid in full to that equivalent in British Pound Sterling (GBP). Chris Watterston reserves the right to withhold project completion until full settlement has been made from Client.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>10. Liability &amp; Warranty Disclaimer</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">Chris Watterston provides design and development Services, and provides a limited forty (40) day warranty with regard to the design or development Services, or fitness of Services offered for a particular purpose. Chris Watterston provides no warranty on print or support Services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">Chris Watterston endeavours to provide Services within given delivery timescale(s) to the best of its ability.