amily-table\" href=\"/get-in-contact\" title=\"Enquire for eCommerce, Website Design and Mobile App solutions\">Let&rsquo;s Talk?</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1670494860),(244,6,1141,'Main Body Three','<div class=\"cols more-posts\">\n    		<div class=\"col newsfeed-entry entry-1\">\n			<div class=\"news-img\" style=\"background-image:url(\'http://www.chriswatterston.com/application/files/cache/967fe8010e8902d3827cb4fd3dcbe42b.jpg\');\"></div>\n			<div class=\"news-content-wrap\">\n				<div class=\"news-content\">\n                    	<h2 class=\"colour-grey type-semibold\">Ford van graphical sign writing</h2>\n          					<p class=\"description colour-grey\">\n													An extension of our relationship with CD Surveys Ltd, they informed us that they have a new fleet of 4 Ford vans that need a touch of branding. I agreed and as a result, we collaborated on the creation and organisation of&hellip;											</p>\n				</div>\n			</div>\n			<a href=\"http://www.chriswatterston.com/case-studies/cd-surveys-ltd-ford-van-graphical-sign-writing\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Continue reading, Ford van graphical sign writing\" class=\"hidden\"></a>\n		</div>\n			<div class=\"col newsfeed-entry entry-2\">\n			<div class=\"news-img\" style=\"background-image:url(\'http://www.chriswatterston.com/application/files/cache/ed878ddfbef74434eaafbb76371b70c7.jpg\');\"></div>\n			<div class=\"news-content-wrap\">\n				<div class=\"news-content\">\n                    	<h2 class=\"colour-grey type-semibold\">Salesian School website design</h2>\n          					<p class=\"description colour-grey\">\n													Contracted with Salesian school for a 12 month period, 3 days a week, I worked literally side-by-side with the Deputy and Assistant Headteachers. After discussing their requirements and needs, I collaborated and designed what&hellip;											</p>\n				</div>\n			</div>\n			<a href=\"http://www.chriswatterston.com/case-studies/salesian-school-website-design\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Continue reading, Salesian School website design\" class=\"hidden\"></a>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n',1513298207),(244,6,1241,'Main Body Two','\n  <script>\n  $(document).ready(function(){\n      $(function () {\n          $(\"#ccm-image-slider-1241\").responsiveSlides({\n              prevText: \"\",   // String: Text for the \"previous\" button\n              nextText: \"\",\n  		  		nav:true,\n  		pager: true,\n  		              timeout: 5000,              speed: 500,              pause: true,                                      });\n      });\n  });\n  </script>\n\n  <div class=\"casestudy-slider ccm-image-slider-container ccm-block-image-slider-pages\" >\n      <div class=\"ccm-image-slider\">\n        <div class=\"ccm-image-slider-inner\">\n                      <ul class=\"rslides\" id=\"ccm-image-slider-1241\">\n                              <li>\n                                    <div class=\"ccm-image-slider-text\">\n                                          <h3 class=\"ccm-image-slider-title type-semibold\">Staff daily day schedule reminder</h3>\n                                        <p>Developed using a combination of HTML, CSS, PHP, MySQL and Google Maps API (obtain static map image of job location) that runs within a bespoke built CRM system. These personalised emails are received by each member of staff as a daily reminder of the job they have been assigned to, at 5AM every weekday. The emails are scheduled and triggered using a Windows BAT script, which executes PHP, which then loops through the HTML, CSS, PHP, MySQL and Google Maps API combination - resulting in a the emails successfully being sent via an external SMTP provider.</p>\r\n                  </div>\n                  <img src=\"/application/files/4515/1272/7596/html-email-cdsurveys-dailyjob.jpg\" alt=\"Staff daily day schedule reminder\" width=\"1879\" height=\"2016\">                </li>\n                              <li>\n                                    <div class=\"ccm-image-slider-text\">\n                                          <h3 class=\"ccm-image-slider-title type-semibold\">Monthly Newsletter</h3>\n                                        <p>Designed within Photoshop, developed locally and then finalised within MailChimp, this monthly newsletter is sent by myself to my client base. It was designed to include minimal images to enable instant email client compatibility, and easy to understand and read in both HTML and plain-text renderings. The design has been built within MailChimp as a template, which then enables the continuation of monthly campaigns that are created and populated throughout the month. The newsletter is received and read within a wide range of devices, meaning that the design was developed to support 100% mobile responsiveness.</p>\r\n                  </div>\n                  <img src=\"/application/files/6615/1272/7936/html-email-chriswatterston-newsletternew.jpg\" alt=\"Monthly Newsletter\" width=\"1879\" height=\"2354\">                </li>\n                              <li>\n                                    <div class=\"ccm-image-slider-text\">\n                                          <h3 class=\"ccm-image-slider-title type-semibold\">Annual Market Round Up Newsletter</h3>\n                                        <p>Content and spoken vision provided by the client, which was then taken and designed within Photoshop, developed locally as a one-off campaign and then imported into Swiftpage. This design was to outline the corporations 2014 annual round up. It was design as a one off campaign and included a high level of images. This meant that image ALT tags needed to be descriptive and discrete the image being &ldquo;blocked&rdquo; by the client. Not much acknowledgment was put into ensuring the plain-text renderings was clear, as this was solely targeting a full HTML render. Due to the nature and design of the newsletter, this particular design was not required to support 100% mobile responsiveness.</p>\r\n                  </div>\n                  <img src=\"/application/files/7215/1272/8054/html-email-moorfields-marketroundup.jpg\" alt=\"Annual Market Round Up Newsletter\" width=\"1879\" height=\"3456\">                </li>\n                              <li>\n                                    <div class=\"ccm-image-slider-text\">\n                                          <h3 class=\"ccm-image-slider-title type-semibold\">Weekly expired quotation</h3>\n                                        <p>Developed using a combination of HTML, CSS, PHP and MySQL that runs within a bespoke built CRM system. This email is received by a particular staff selection (directors and finance) to list the expired quotations that the system has processed. This notification is received on the closure of every week, at approx 4:30PM on Friday afternoon. The email is scheduled and triggered using a Windows BAT script, which executes PHP, which then loops through the HTML, CSS, PHP and MySQL combination - resulting in a the email successfully being sent via an external SMTP provider.</p>\r\n                  </div>\n                  <img src=\"/application/files/6915/1272/7649/html-email-cdsurveys-expiredquotes.jpg\" alt=\"Weekly expired quotation\" width=\"1879\" height=\"2016\">                </li>\n                              <li>\n                                    <div class=\"ccm-image-slider-text\">\n                                          <h3 class=\"ccm-image-slider-title type-semibold\">Latest Update Newsletter</h3>\n                                        <p>Content and spoken vision provided by the client, which was then taken and finalised within Photoshop, developed locally and then finalised within MailChimp. This design was to outline the corporations main latest news, as well as additional small updates. It was design to provide an even amount of copy and images. The design had been imported within MailChimp as a template, which then enabled the continuation of successful campaigns. The newsletter is received and read within a wide range of devices, but was not required to support 100% mobile responsiveness.</p>\r\n                  </div>\n                  <img src=\"/application/files/5615/1272/8110/html-email-moorfields-media13columns.jpg\" alt=\"Latest Update Newsletter\" width=\"1879\" height=\"2911\">                </li>\n                              <li>\n                                    <div class=\"ccm-image-slider-text\">\n                                          <h3 class=\"ccm-image-slider-title type-semibold\">Weekly snapshot of complete staff schedule</h3>\n                                        <p>Developed using a combination of HTML, CSS, PHP and MySQL that runs within a bespoke built CRM system. This email is received by a particular staff selection (directors) to provide an in-email snapshot of the closing weeks staff schedule. This notification is received on the closure of every week, at approx 4:30PM on Friday afternoon. The email is scheduled and triggered using a Windows BAT script, which executes PHP, which then loops through the HTML, CSS, PHP and MySQL combination - resulting in a the email successfully being sent via an external SMTP provider.</p>\r\n                  </div>\n                  <img src=\"/application/files/4815/1272/7866/html-email-cdsurveys-jobboard.jpg\" alt=\"Weekly snapshot of complete staff schedule\" width=\"1879\" height=\"2016\">                </li>\n                              <li>\n                                    <div class=\"ccm-image-slider-text\">\n                                          <h3 class=\"ccm-image-slider-title type-semibold\">Latest Update Newsletter</h3>\n                                        <p>Designed within Photoshop, developed locally and then finalised within MailChimp, this monthly newsletter was (old version) sent by myself to my client base. The design has been built within MailChimp as a template, which then enabled the continuation of monthly campaigns that are created and populated throughout the month.</p>\r\n                  </div>\n                  <img src=\"/application/files/2715/1272/7980/html-email-chriswatterston-newsletterold.jpg\" alt=\"Latest Update Newsletter\" width=\"1879\" height=\"2354\">                </li>\n                              <li>\n                                    <div class=\"ccm-image-slider-text\">\n                                          <h3 class=\"ccm-image-slider-title type-semibold\">Weekly overdue invoices</h3>\n                                        <p>Developed using a combination of HTML, CSS, PHP and MySQL that runs within a bespoke built CRM system. This email is received by a particular staff selection (directors and finance) to list the outstanding invoices within the system. This notification is received on the opening and mid point (Monday and Wednesday) of every week,&nbsp; at approx 6AM. The email is scheduled and triggered using a Windows BAT script, which executes PHP, which then loops through the HTML, CSS, PHP and MySQL combination - resulting in a the email successfully being sent via an external SMTP provider.</p>\r\n                  </div>\n                  <img src=\"/application/files/5115/1272/7682/html-email-cdsurveys-overdueinvoices.jpg\" alt=\"Weekly overdue invoices\" width=\"1879\" height=\"2016\">                </li>\n                              <li>\n                                    <div class=\"ccm-image-slider-text\">\n                                          <h3 class=\"ccm-image-slider-title type-semibold\">Industry Update Newsletter</h3>\n                                        <p>Wire-framed by the client and handed over, was then taken and finalised within Photoshop, developed locally and then finalised within Swiftpage. This design was to outline the corporations latest news and updates. It was design to provide more copy that images, meaning that it was easy to understand and read in both HTML and plain-text renderings. The design had been imported within Swiftpage as a template, which then enabled the continuation of successful campaigns. The newsletter is received and read within a wide range of devices, but was not required to support 100% mobile responsiveness.</p>\r\n                  </div>\n                  <img src=\"/application/files/9815/1272/8030/html-email-moorfields-13columns.jpg\" alt=\"Industry Update Newsletter\" width=\"1879\" height=\"2354\">                </li>\n                              <li>\n                                    <div class=\"ccm-image-slider-text\">\n                                          <h3 class=\"ccm-image-slider-title type-semibold\">SaaS Password Reset Notification</h3>\n                                        <p>Developed using a combination of HTML, CSS, PHP and MySQL that ran within the backend of a SaaS system, this particular email send consumers unique notifications depending on their actions. This notification can be triggered at any time by using the SaaS, resulting in a the email successfully being sent by using the PHP mail function.&nbsp;</p>\r\n                  </div>\n                  <img src=\"/application/files/8315/1272/8139/html-email-mychildsdiary-passwordreset.jpg\" alt=\"SaaS Password Reset Notification\" width=\"1879\" height=\"1559\">                </li>\n                          </ul>\n                  </div>\n      </div>\n  </div>\n\n',1670494860),(245,1,47,'Main','<h1 class=\"colour-white type-semibold type-uppercase\">Contact.</h1>\r\n',1670754471),(245,1,51,'Main','<h1 class=\"colour-white type-semibold type-uppercase\">Instagram.</h1>\r\n',1670754471),(245,1,62,'Main','<ul class=\"nav\"><li class=\"\"><a href=\"http://www.chriswatterston.com/\" target=\"_self\" class=\"\">Home</a></li><li class=\"\"><a href=\"http://www.chriswatterston.com/designer-developer-solutions-and-services\" target=\"_self\" class=\"\">Solutions</a></li><li class=\"\"><a href=\"http://www.