">\n				<div class=\"news-content\">\n                    	<h2 class=\"colour-grey type-semibold\">A much needed Spotify widget for the Notification Center</h2>\n          					<p class=\"description colour-grey\">\n													Since installing the new operating system, OS X Yosemite, like many I&#039;ve noticed a hell of a lot of new great features and design. But, being an every day MacBook user, I&#039;m finding some pretty cool, but some also pretty&hellip;											</p>\n				</div>\n			</div>\n			<a href=\"http://www.chriswatterston.com/blog/a-much-needed-spotify-widget-for-the-notification-center\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Continue reading, A much needed Spotify widget for the Notification Center\" class=\"hidden\"></a>\n		</div>\n			<div class=\"col newsfeed-entry entry-2\">\n			<div class=\"news-img\" style=\"background-image:url(\'http://www.chriswatterston.com/application/files/cache/a47208abdba298c6c1ddd8ef66e04177.jpg\');\"></div>\n			<div class=\"news-content-wrap\">\n				<div class=\"news-content\">\n                    	<h2 class=\"colour-grey type-semibold\">Starting 2016 with old challenges</h2>\n          					<p class=\"description colour-grey\">\n													Like every Tom, Dick and Harry in the land, I set myself new targets and challenges at the start of every year. Do I ever achieve them, behave yourself! It&rsquo;s so frustrating telling you that, but even more so with myself for&hellip;											</p>\n				</div>\n			</div>\n			<a href=\"http://www.chriswatterston.com/blog/starting-2016-old-challenges\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Continue reading, Starting 2016 with old challenges\" class=\"hidden\"></a>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n',1512988371),(245,1,1242,'Main Body','<h2><b>M&amp;S - Paddington &amp; The Christmas Visitor</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>M&amp;S show the gift of giving when Paddington assists a burglar, that Paddington mistakes for Santa, delivering all the presents (that he had just stolen) to the the children around the neighbourhood. After their night together, the burglar takes a turn and realises that the gift of giving if a much warm hearted way.<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/KfaSxIkLslE\">https://youtu.be/KfaSxIkLslE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>John Lewis - #MozTheMonster</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>John Lewis are showing that just a little thought into a gift, can be truly beautiful. Like many children, the boy doesn&rsquo;t get much sleep because the &ldquo;monster under the bed&rdquo; keeps him awake, and after time it starts to have an impact. The monster gives the gift of a night light up to help the boy sleep, putting his mind at rest about the monster.<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/Jw1Y-zhQURU\">https://youtu.be/Jw1Y-zhQURU</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Asda - Best Christmas Ever</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m not sure what message I get from Asda, apart from that there food gets made in a unique Elf factory. It somewhat reminds me of Charlie and the Chocolate Factory. A second watch gives the impressions of maybe they wont to show how much dedication they put in the quality of their food, maybe?<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/Rd9wKCy1pAE\">https://youtu.be/Rd9wKCy1pAE</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Debenhams - #YouShall Find Your Fairytale Christmas (Part 1 &amp; 2)</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This is like watching a series on TV, Cinderella type cliff hangers and all that. A story line that relates to reality, social media sharing their story to help find her shoe and their reunion, it leaves your heart warm and waiting for your wedding invite. Stunning.<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/fyNhzFYP3ts\">https://youtu.be/fyNhzFYP3ts</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Sainsbury&rsquo;s - #everybitofChristmas</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Sainsbury&rsquo;s theme this years is a catchy one, although I likely won&rsquo;t be learning it. But I&rsquo;m not sure what the message is here - any ideas?<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/WU50dLLy7Cw\">https://youtu.be/WU50dLLy7Cw</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Tesco - Turkey, Every Which Way</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The title of Tesco&rsquo;s Christmas advert speaks for itself and is enough to warm&nbsp;the&nbsp;cockles&nbsp;of one&#39;s heart. Tesco shows that whatever family relation you are; religion, race, culture, you are welcome at Tesco. Everyone is welcome to Christmas and to celebrate.<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/qSUkAURUU1I\">https://youtu.be/qSUkAURUU1I</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Barbour - The Snowman and The Snowdog</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve always been a fan of Barbour, their range shows quality. Watching their advert, they tell a story about a Snowman that gave a little boy a dog for Christmas. Years pass and the little boy turns into an Adult, who turns into a parent, who remembers the Snowman and at this giving time of the year. Christmas morning arrives, and so does the much loved and giving Snowman, but this year the not so little boy&rsquo;s family gives back to the Snowman, showing that his gifts were never forgotten - It just happens that this gift is a Barbour waxed coat!<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/vkIjXeYBit0\">https://youtu.be/vkIjXeYBit0</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Argos - #ReadyForTakeOff</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Argos will pulls out all the stops to ensure delivery of your Christmas. Even if it means side swiping 4 meters behind a taking of jet plane, in an open top &ldquo;golf buggy&rdquo;!<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/WNqm-sgz86Y\">https://youtu.be/WNqm-sgz86Y</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Aldi - Kevin The Carrot</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Christmas is a time for loved ones to come together. Aldi shows this with Kevin, the carrot, and his ordeal across an express trains dining table, with an impressive spread. He eventfully falls in the arms of his &ldquo;love at first site&rdquo;, and saves her from peeing herself.<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/iJGpOYKXcSE\">https://youtu.be/iJGpOYKXcSE</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Lidl - Mince Pie Maverick</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This advert is directed towards me. I&rsquo;m a bit of a mince pie fan boy, and just watching this makes me weak at the knees - just the thought of a piping hot mince pie with cold cream, oh sh*t! The price seems alright for mince pies, too.<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/GIn-52yrrPI\">https://youtu.be/GIn-52yrrPI</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>House of Fraser&nbsp;- Bring Merry Back</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We all have that annoying someone, whether it&rsquo;s around Christmas or just generally every day. House of Fraser shows that we should push that feeling aside and bring Merry back with a smile, gift and love.<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/2PvPqn4dSYc\">https://youtu.be/2PvPqn4dSYc</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Toys &#39;R&#39; Us - Geoffrey the Part Time Reindeer</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Toys &lsquo;R&rsquo; Us shows that they can provide every gift under one roof, and it seems that even the reindeers can&rsquo;t resist. Thankfully the long and loyal Geoffery is here to help again, from stacking the shelves to putting presents down our chimneys.<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/B72y_OByf_4\">https://youtu.be/B72y_OByf_4</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Currys PC World - Ahmed&rsquo;s Run</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This one brought a smile to my face as it can relate to real life. A Currys PC World employee is trialing products prior to selling them in store, enabling him to understand how and what they can be used for. I thought this was a good one as it had comedy roots.<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/9kGTIaoyTOc\">https://youtu.be/9kGTIaoyTOc</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Co-op - Christmas is coming together</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Another heart warning advert about coming together. Similar to that of Tesco, it shows different religions, race, cultures. All coming together and enjoying this time of the year, showing that &ldquo;love is the greatest thing&rdquo;.<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/2CHM9W59slA\">https://youtu.be/2CHM9W59slA</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1670754471),(245,2,64,'Main','<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"/application/themes/chriswatterst